 {"id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","title":"Port obligation, record, session, and link public parity","description":"Rust exposes rich obligation and record families plus session and link surfaces used for diagnostics, proofs, and long-lived coordination. ANSI C currently has only partial lower-level pieces, leaving a large user-facing and correctness-story gap.","design":"Implement public record types, obligation helpers beyond the raw kernel path, and session/link coordination APIs. Keep observability, monitor, and evidence-sink work in a dedicated sibling task so this bead stays implementable without losing scope.","acceptance_criteria":"A. The missing public record, obligation, session, and link module families exist and integrate with runtime flows.\\nB. Tests cover record lifecycle, session/link behavior, and obligation misuse.\\nC. At least one e2e or smoke lane exercises a realistic session/link flow with detailed logs and failure summaries.","notes":"Coordinate with the new observability/evidence task under the same epic so proof artifacts and runtime records share one coherent contract.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:22.799210276Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T20:52:58.448641833Z","closed_at":"2026-03-14T20:52:58.448232799Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","evidence","obligation","record","session"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:53.754722768Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:54.563725663Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:55.384692776Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:22.799210276Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.5.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:26.765562199Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.5.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:27.933998191Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.5.4","title":"Port observability, monitor, evidence, and evidence-sink public parity","description":"The reopened backlog still underrepresented upstream observability and monitoring surfaces: monitor.rs, evidence.rs, evidence_sink.rs, and the broader observability story promised by the crate. ANSI C cannot claim user-facing parity if proof collection and runtime observability remain hidden inside ad hoc diagnostics.","design":"Implement public observability, monitor, evidence, and evidence-sink modules that collect structured diagnostic material, integrate with trace/runtime state, and feed both operator reports and deterministic failure artifacts. This bead should be explicit about detailed logging, artifact schema, and verdict derivation so future users can trust the output.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public monitor/observability/evidence/evidence-sink modules exist with coherent contracts.\\nB. Unit tests cover evidence accumulation, monitor thresholding, verdict aggregation, and negative/error paths.\\nC. At least one logged e2e lane emits rich evidence artifacts and human-readable summaries that a maintainer can use without reproducing the failure immediately.","notes":"Primary upstream references: src/monitor.rs, src/evidence.rs, src/evidence_sink.rs, and observability exports in src/lib.rs. Coordinate closely with bd-yx9r.3 and bd-yx9r.6.2 so artifact formats stay consistent.","status":"in_progress","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:51.773247510Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T22:59:45.690683053Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","evidence","monitor","observability"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:08.165983935Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:09.520212567Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:10.847734375Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.5","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:27:51.773247510Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.5.4","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.5.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:28:37.566693705Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-yx9r.6","title":"Runtime, trace, lab, and util completion beyond current kernel scaffolding","description":"The current C tree has scheduler/cancel/timer/quiescence and some runtime-side helpers, but the upstream crate still exposes much broader runtime/reactor/trace/lab/util surfaces: runtime builders, local runtimes, spawn_blocking, task handles/tables, deadline monitors, advanced trace analysis, replayers/minimizers, lab network/http/meta tooling, and deterministic utilities.","design":"This epic should close the gap between a functioning kernel and the broader runtime/tooling system users expect from the crate.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Missing runtime/trace/lab/util public families are represented concretely in ANSI C.\\nB. Determinism, replay, and diagnostic claims are backed by richer trace/lab evidence than the current kernel-only lanes.\\nC. Higher-surface networking/protocol work can build on these runtime/tooling primitives.","notes":"Primary upstream references: src/runtime/*, src/runtime/reactor/*, src/trace/*, src/lab/*, src/util/*.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:23.700831656Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-13T20:41:06.166054052Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","lab","runtime","trace"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:23.700831656Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:02.497407280Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:03.461678881Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:39:04.462855809Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-yx9r.6.1","title":"Complete runtime builder/state/reactor/local/spawn_blocking/deadline-monitor surfaces","description":"Port the missing runtime-side user-facing surfaces: builder/local runtime APIs, environment/config-driven setup, stored-task and handle tables, deadline monitors, sharded state, spawn_blocking, and reactor registration/backends in a form that ANSI C users can actually exercise.","design":"Treat this as the substrate for network, server, and higher-protocol stacks. Implementation may use profile-specific adapters, but semantics and diagnostics must remain explicit.","acceptance_criteria":"A. Public runtime APIs cover builder/local/reactor/blocking/deadline/state surfaces with documented profile behavior.\\nB. Unit and integration tests cover registration, wakeups, blocking pool handoff, deadline misses, and fail-closed unsupported-profile behavior.\\nC. Logged smoke scripts exercise at least one native reactor path and one deterministic/lab path.","notes":"This task is a major blocker for real networking/protocol parity.","status":"in_progress","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:24.627046422Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-14T22:59:29.113006016Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["crate-parity","reactor","runtime"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:56.170324638Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:56.988853706Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-13T22:26:57.785428563Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-yx9r.6.1","depends_on_id":"bd-yx9r.6","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-13T20:38:24.627046422Z","created_by"